3.1 Python Style Compliance

•
Rule: Follow PEP 8 style guidelines for Python code

•
Implementation:

•
Use snake_case for variables, functions, methods, modules

•
Use PascalCase for classes

•
Use UPPER_CASE for constants

•
Cursor IDE should enforce PEP 8 compliance



3.2 Database Entity Naming

•
Rule: Use consistent naming for database entities

•
Implementation:

•
Table names: plural, lowercase, snake_case

•
Column names: singular, snake_case

•
Primary keys: id or <entity>_id

•
Foreign keys: <referenced_entity>_id

•
Cursor IDE should validate database naming conventions



3.3 API Endpoint Naming

•
Rule: Use consistent naming for API endpoints and commands

•
Implementation:

•
Command names: UPPER_CASE, descriptive verbs

•
Parameters: camelCase for JSON properties

•
Status codes: UPPER_CASE, descriptive adjectives

•
Cursor IDE should validate command naming conventions



3.4 GUI Element Naming

•
Rule: Use consistent naming for GUI elements

•
Implementation:

•
Widget variables: descriptive, with type suffix (e.g., status_label)

•
Action methods: verb_noun format (e.g., update_status)

•
Form classes: descriptive, with Form suffix (e.g., AnimalConfigForm)

•
Cursor IDE should suggest naming corrections for GUI elements



3.5 Hardware Interface Naming

•
Rule: Use consistent naming for hardware interfaces

•
Implementation:

•
Port names: descriptive of function, not hardware specifics

•
Controller classes: descriptive, with Controller suffix

•
Configuration keys: match physical labeling where applicable

